        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 5:32AM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 532 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Pike Road, or 10 miles southeast of Montgomery, moving east at 40
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Montgomery, Prattville, Tuskegee, Union Springs, Milstead, Pike Road,
Shorter, Franklin, Montgomery Zoo, Boylston, Hyundai Motors Of
Alabama, Auburn University In Montgomery, Franklin Field, Lake
Tuskegee, Woodcrest, Maxwell Air Force Base, Snowdoun, Davisville,
Waugh, and Lagoon Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
